gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Magic 113, Suns 98
gameRecap.excerpt: Despite Devin Booker’s 44 points (17-26 FG), the Suns fall to the Magic, 113-98. Paolo Banchero led the way for the Magic with 26 points, four rebounds and seven assists, while Moritz Wagner added 16 points and 12 rebounds in the victory. Devin Booker tallied his fifth 40+ point game of the season, and 30th of his career. Kevin Durant reached 28K points on a three-pointer with 11:31 remaining in the fourth quarter. The Magic improve to 24-22 on the season, while the Suns fall to 26-20.
